# =============================================================================
# Al Hewal — Git attributes
#
# Normalise text files to LF + UTF-8 so checkouts are consistent across
# Windows, mac, and the CI runners. Critical for `database.types.ts`,
# which is regenerated via `pnpm supabase gen types ... > <file>` from
# PowerShell — PowerShell's default redirection writes UTF-16 LE + CRLF,
# which Git then flags as binary and which breaks ESLint/tsc. The rule
# below tells Git to treat all *.ts files as text with LF endings (Git
# itself doesn't re-encode UTF-16, but the explicit `text` attribute
# combined with the contributor pattern documented in
# `docs/PHASE_3_RUNBOOK.md` §5 keeps regens consistent).
# =============================================================================

* text=auto eol=lf

# Generated / large lockfiles — Git default detection is fine.
pnpm-lock.yaml -diff

# Binary assets — explicit so Git never tries to munge line endings.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.webp binary
*.avif binary
*.svg text eol=lf

# Source text — explicit for the editorially-important file types.
*.ts text eol=lf
*.tsx text eol=lf
*.js text eol=lf
*.mjs text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
*.md text eol=lf
*.css text eol=lf
*.sql text eol=lf
*.yml text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf
